title: TV highlights: Kaitlyn makes her final choice in season finale of ‘The Bachelorette’
text:
Kaitlyn Bristowe in the season finale of “The Bachelorette.” (Rick Rowell/ABC) By — Lauren McEwen July 26 at 4:54 PM All times Eastern.
FINALE WATCH: Kaitlyn is forced to choose between Shawn and Nick in the season 11 finale of “The Bachelorette” (ABC at 8 p.m.).
The Top 18 dancers compete on “So You Think You Can Dance” (Fox at 8).
The Amazing Allison, Norman Ng, Mac King and Austin Janik try to trick the veteran illusionists on “Penn & Teller: Fool Us” (CW at 8).
The master bakers make Hello Kitty-inspired creations on “Cake Wars” (Food Network at 8).
Director Michele Josue’s award-winning 2013 documentary “Matt Shepard is a Friend of Mine” (Logo TV at 9) details the life and death of the her friend Matthew Shepard, the gay college student who was brutally murdered in Laramie, Wyo., in 1998.
T.I. opens a new restaurant, and Tameka joins Niq Niq in the studio on “T.I. and Tiny: The Family Hustle” (VH1 at 9:30).
Actress Kate Winslet accompanies Bear on a paramotor trip through the Snowdonia region of Wales on “Running Wild With Bear Grylls” (NBC at 10).
“POV” (PBS at 10) profiles a group of Chilean women who have been meeting for monthly tea parties for the past six decades.
The Lehwald family has a New York Thanksgiving on “Becoming Us” (ABC Family at 10).
On “The Making of the Mob” (AMC at 10), Luciano gains control of Vito Genovese’s Italian heroin ring and heads to Cuba to join Meyer Lansky at a mob summit meeting.
Demetrio gets a new engine and Roberto discovers that the Bel-Air’s pistons and crankshaft are busted on “Cuban Chrome” (Discovery at 10).
On “UnReal” (Lifetime at 10), Rachel faces the consequences of her impulsive behavior, she and Quinn worry about their careers, and three contestants have romantic dates at Adam’s vineyard.
The “Southern Fried Road Trip” (Food Network at 10) brothers celebrate Bobby’s birthday with a trip to Louisiana, where they sample alligator allemond, boudin balls, King Cake cheesecake and more.
On “Teen Wolf” (MTV at 10), Scott and his friends suffer strange side effects after taking Dr. Valack’s advice.
Tom Cruise and Dick Cavett stop by “The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon” (NBC at 11:30). Musical guest Ashley Monroe performs and Buddy Guy joins The Roots.
— Lauren McEwen
